JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways is optimistic its five-year plan will come to the rescue. The airline's financial situation is dire. It's not made a profit in the past few years.The airline has government guarantees totalling R19-billion.READ: SAA running at a lossIt s now in talks with its lenders to renegotiate its loans.By the end of June, R9-billion will be due. Only one lender has said the airline must pay back its loan.Details of several initiatives will be announced once the plan has been by government.eNCA